    <span class="subtitleGreen">HOW IT WORKS </span>
    <br>
    <br>
    <span class="main_copy_font">Current washing machines use about 3 gallons of water per pound of laundry washed. With the technology that we will be taking advantage of, current projections and real world applications have made it possible to use approximately 1 gallon of water per pound of laundry. 
        <br>
        <br>
        At My Fresh Shirt, we didn’t want to stop at just saving two gallons of water, we wanted to find a way to give it to someone who could really use it…and we have. Our My Fresh Water program keeps track of how much water you have saved by doing your wash & fold laundry with us. Then by way of algorithm, we are able to determine what it would cost to donate a gallon of water based on your actual usage.
        <br>
        <br>
        Did you know that 42,000 deaths occur every week from lack of safe water and basic sanitation, where 90% are children under 5 years old?
        <br>
        <br>
       Contributions to MY FRESH WATER fund the purchase of wells through an alliance formed with charity: water. Each well will provide a small community with safe & clean drinking water. Since August 2006, charity: water has proven their commitment by building more than 250 wells that have provided clean drinking water to more than 150,000 people. It’s a proven equation for a dire situation. And by using My Fresh Shirt’s wash &amp; fold service you too can help conserve water and provide life.  
        Visit <a href="http://www.charityis.org" target="_blank">www.charityis.org</a> to 
        learn more today.
    </span>
